{
  "stem": "1568.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If he would think logically, he would know, but that-- that was his only straw in his [? head. ?] I came back and told my dad and brother what I saw and what was involved.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[SIGHS] They didn't let us back for the next three days.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then we found out that three days later, the rest of the people were sent out, that including my mother and sister.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they went to Treblinka and that's where I lost them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[SIGHS] After everybody was sent out, we were sent back to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I guess from about 14,000, 15,000 people, we were just about 1,000 people left, only the people who worked.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And again, necessities of our life-- like in any tragedy, life has to go on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We-- we continued to work and live there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] By the end of '40-- '43, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] we were-- the ghetto and Tomaszow was closed completely.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We were sent out to a working camp called Blizyn.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] In Blizyn, again, the-- we started feeling the-- the-- I mean, in ghetto, the difficulties were getting bad already at the tail end.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You remember, the first time, a kosher home, my mom somehow got a hold of some horse meat and tried to cook it and found out it wasn't that terrific.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So-- but it still is was liveable.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In the camp, you were started out with two rations a day.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You got some soup at lunchtime and some bread at night, and this was your daily necessities.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Again, I and my brother went to work in a knitting factory.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We made stockings for soldiers, you know, under the supervision of a German kapo.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
